7)
Write a Java program to check if a given number is a palindrome or not. 
A number is a palindrome if it remains the same when its digits are reversed.

package basic.Palindrome;
public class Palindrome
{
    public static void main(String [] args)
    {
        int number = Integer.parseInt(args[0]);
        int digit;
        int reverseNumber = 0;
        int orginalNumber = number ;

        // Reverse the number logic
        while(number != 0){
        digit = number % 10 ; // we will get last digit of the num = 121 i.e : 1
        reverseNumber = reverseNumber * 10 + digit ; // 0 * 10 + 1 = 1
        number = number / 10 ; // it will remove last digit of num i.e : 12_
        }
        //check panlindrome
        if(orginalNumber == reverseNumber)
        {
            System.out.println(reverseNumber + " is a palindrome");
        }
        else 
        {
            System.out.println(reverseNumber + " is not a palindrome");
        }
    }
}
output :
C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\all codes\java\19,22>javac -d . Palindrome.java

C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\all codes\java\19,22>java basic.Palindrome.Palindrome 121
121 is a palindrome

