8)
// A shopkeeper buys a TV set for Rs. 32,500 and sells it at a profit of 27%.
//  Apart from this a GST of 5% is charged. Display total selling price, profit along with GST charge.
package basic.SellingTv;
public class SellingTv 
{
    public static void main(String [] args)
    {
        int tvPrice = Integer.parseInt(args [0]); 
        double profit = Double.parseDouble(args [1]); // 27% -- 0.27
        double gst = Double.parseDouble(args [2]); // 5% -- 0.05
        double totalSellingPrice = (tvPrice + (tvPrice*profit) + (gst)) ;
        

        System.out.println(totalSellingPrice + "it is total selling price of TV");
    }
}
output : 
C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\all codes\java\19,22,23>javac -d . SellingTv.java

C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\all codes\java\19,22,23>java basic.SellingTv.SellingTv 32500 0.27 0.05
41275.05it is total selling price of TV
